        "sections": [
            {
                "name": "Willing Hosts",
                "type": "section",
                "sections": [],
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Pathfinder #152: Legacy of the Lost God",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Pathfinder #152: Legacy of the Lost God pg. 81",
                            "alt": "Pathfinder #152: Legacy of the Lost God pg. 81",
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zrd?"
                        },
                        "page": 81
                    }
                ],
                "subtype": "sidebar",
                "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                "image": {
                    "type": "image",
                    "name": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                },
                "html": "Some actors who have felt the touch of a muse phantom come to relish and even desire the feeling of giving oneself over to what they consider a divine theatrical spirit. Such willing hosts voluntarily and routinely let themselves become possessed by a muse phantom, or even allow the spirit to reside within their body permanently. This symbiotic relationship allows the actor to advance their acting career and the phantom to continue performing to admiring masses."
            }
        ],
        "level": 5,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Uncommon",
                "class": "uncommon",
                "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can\u2019t be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
